    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't think we're going to be supporting this feature -- in the same way that Geth does not natively support this feature. In OVM 2.0, Optimistic Ethereum is extremely close to \"just Geth\". This means that your testing pattern should basically be the same -- test your contracts in Hardhat and then deploy to OE. I think we can close this since that testing pattern does allow you to use console.log.",
